This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new benchmark for measuring the performance of transfer learning and few-shot learning algorithms in the RL domain. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RL is a subfield of AI. The use of video game franchise Sonic the Hedgehog suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.GR (Graphics) as these fields often involve analyzing and processing visual data. Finally, the evaluation of baseline algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as RL is often used in robotics applications.
